WEBVTT

00:01.083 --> 00:02.625
Family meeting
in the dining room.

00:03.083 --> 00:04.417
The hell's a family meeting?

00:04.625 --> 00:05.792
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:07.750 --> 00:09.542
I stole two bags of heroin,

00:09.625 --> 00:11.166
and I planted them
in Carrie's car.

00:11.625 --> 00:12.500
I've been suspended.

00:12.709 --> 00:13.875
HELEN: I don't know
what the hell to say.

00:14.125 --> 00:16.750
Oh, wait, it just came to me.
That was stupid!

00:17.625 --> 00:18.542
What's wrong with you?!

00:18.625 --> 00:20.041
SIOBHAN SHEEHAN:
Kevin despised you.

00:20.709 --> 00:23.333
So, yes, I want my son back
for me but also for Kevin.

00:23.667 --> 00:25.583
Because he deserves a lot better
than you.

00:26.625 --> 00:27.959
What are you doing
Saturday night?

00:28.291 --> 00:29.875
Are you asking me out on a date,
Zabel?

00:30.500 --> 00:32.667
I find out that the last person
to speak with Eric McMenamin

00:32.750 --> 00:34.208
on the night she's murdered
potentially had

00:34.291 --> 00:36.625
an inappropriate relationship
with another young girl.

00:36.834 --> 00:38.458
You can understand why I'd be
concerned.

00:40.542 --> 00:42.208
SPEAKER:
No one can hear you in here.

00:42.458 --> 00:43.542
Who are you?

00:44.583 --> 00:46.000
I'm Katie Bailey.

00:57.041 --> 01:00.542
(SPARKS CRACKLING)

01:29.917 --> 01:32.083
-DREW SHEEHAN: Gran!
-SIOBHAN SHEEHAN: Drew?

01:32.166 --> 01:33.458
-DREW: Gran!
-Hold on.

01:33.542 --> 01:35.834
-SIOBHAN: Drew, come here.
-I'll be right out.

01:35.917 --> 01:37.667
DREW: Yeah, I don't like it.
It's too dark.

01:37.750 --> 01:38.792
It's okay. It's okay.

01:38.875 --> 01:40.166
MARE SHEEHAN:
It's okay, here I come.

01:40.250 --> 01:41.959
-Here. Here's Gran. Here's Gran.
-It's okay, buddy. Come on.

01:42.041 --> 01:44.959
There we go. I got you,
I got you. Hold on to me.

01:45.041 --> 01:46.625
Do we have any real flashlights?

01:46.709 --> 01:49.125
Uh, yeah, they're, um--
they're by the sink.

01:49.208 --> 01:52.041
-HELEN FAHEY: Only one works.
-MARE: What about candles?

01:52.125 --> 01:55.041
Um, yeah.
I think we got a few.

01:55.125 --> 01:56.709
-DREW: My turtle.
-What?

01:56.792 --> 01:59.125
-I left him on the floor.
-Okay.

01:59.208 --> 02:01.291
Christ, he's probably
shitting all over the place.

02:01.375 --> 02:03.125
Okay. There you go.
Go with Nana.

02:03.208 --> 02:06.458
-Take my phone, all right.
-Gran didn't mean to say "shit."

02:06.542 --> 02:08.625
-Here, Nana. Matches.
-Thank you, sweetie. Thank you.

02:08.709 --> 02:10.125
-FRANK SHEEHAN: Everyone okay?
-(HELEN GASPS)

02:10.208 --> 02:12.000
-FRANK: I got some
extra batteries.
-SIOBHAN: Hey, Dad.

02:12.083 --> 02:14.250
Hey, it's Pop Pop.
He brought batteries!

02:14.333 --> 02:15.417
How are you, bud?

02:15.500 --> 02:17.166
Yeah, we're gonna go outside
and look at the moon.

02:17.250 --> 02:19.166
-FRANK: Oh. Fun.
-We're gonna light candles.

02:19.250 --> 02:20.959
LORI ROSS:
Bring that one in your room.

02:21.041 --> 02:22.875
-MOIRA ROSS: Thank you.
-LORI: Mm-hmm.

02:23.750 --> 02:25.709
JOHN ROSS:
It's gonna be okay, Ryan.

02:25.792 --> 02:28.417
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

02:28.500 --> 02:30.083
It's our secret, all right?

02:34.542 --> 02:35.709
Only us.

02:37.083 --> 02:38.959
-Hmm?
-RYAN ROSS: Mm-hmm.

02:52.750 --> 02:53.917
(SNIFFS)

02:55.250 --> 02:59.750
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

03:22.291 --> 03:23.500
OFFICER TRAMMEL:
Oh, God.

03:29.250 --> 03:32.375
Seven-five-two-two to Delcom.
Expedite E.M.S.

03:32.458 --> 03:34.792
I'm at the scene of the accident
on Panel Road.

03:34.875 --> 03:37.709
Victim's ID is Betty Carroll.
No pulse.

03:38.917 --> 03:40.208
How are things with Faye?

03:41.000 --> 03:42.709
(INHALES) Hmm.

03:43.667 --> 03:45.875
Not totally great at the moment.

03:46.500 --> 03:47.542
I'm sorry.

03:49.458 --> 03:52.917
Don't be. We'll figure it out.

03:53.000 --> 03:56.500
(EXHALES) Been through worse,
we'll get through this.

04:00.333 --> 04:01.333
How are you?

04:02.583 --> 04:04.834
I feel like I don't ask you
that enough these days.

04:06.959 --> 04:09.375
It's fine, Dad, really.
(CHUCKLES)

04:09.458 --> 04:11.709
No, sweetie. It's not fine.

04:13.375 --> 04:16.542
(EXHALES) And for so long, uh...

04:18.166 --> 04:19.208
your mother and I were

04:19.291 --> 04:21.041
so wrapped up
in our own crap and...

04:23.208 --> 04:24.417
Kevin's issues.

04:26.750 --> 04:29.083
I feel like we forgot
to ask you how you're doing.

04:31.375 --> 04:33.625
I just take for granted
that you're okay,

04:33.709 --> 04:35.375
and that's not fair, Siobhan.

04:36.875 --> 04:38.834
I'm not gonna do that
anymore, okay?

04:43.834 --> 04:44.875
(SNIFFLES)

04:48.125 --> 04:49.375
I met someone.

04:50.875 --> 04:54.166
-FRANK: You met someone?
-Mm-hmm.

04:54.250 --> 04:55.917
MARE: Fucking turtle.

04:56.834 --> 05:00.250
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:15.542 --> 05:18.875
(INDISTINCT CHATTER CONTINUES)

05:25.917 --> 05:31.125
-MARE: What day is it, Kev?
-KEVIN SHEEHAN: Today is...

05:31.583 --> 05:33.250
Saturday.

05:34.125 --> 05:35.917
-MARE: August...
-August...

05:36.000 --> 05:37.834
-MARE: ...fourteen.
-...fourteen!

05:37.917 --> 05:38.875
MARE: (CHUCKLES) Right.

05:38.959 --> 05:40.875
MARE: And what's special
about today?

05:40.959 --> 05:43.291
KEVIN: It's my birthday.

05:43.375 --> 05:46.875
Fine breeze and some fine water.

05:46.959 --> 05:49.959
As you can see,
the lake behind us.

05:50.041 --> 05:51.458
Follow me, Mom.

05:51.542 --> 05:54.834
Let's jump in together.
One, two...

05:54.917 --> 05:57.625
-MARE: Two, three!  (LAUGHS)  Hey!
-KEVIN: ...three!

06:00.041 --> 06:02.250
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

06:07.875 --> 06:10.583
Kevin was pretty normal
little kid, yeah?

06:11.166 --> 06:13.458
Funny, silly, active.

06:15.291 --> 06:18.417
We got the Tourette's diagnosis
when he was eight.

06:18.500 --> 06:21.834
Soon after,
the mood disorder emerged.

06:22.917 --> 06:23.959
He'd...

06:24.917 --> 06:26.709
he'd hit his sister, hit me,

06:26.792 --> 06:30.083
explode into violent tantrums
over the smallest things.

06:30.166 --> 06:32.709
And did his behavior
ever frighten you?

06:35.083 --> 06:38.166
Sometimes... yeah.

06:38.250 --> 06:42.792
Did you try any counseling or...
perhaps some medication?

06:42.875 --> 06:45.667
(CHUCKLES) Oh, God.
What wasn't he put on?

06:45.750 --> 06:49.834
Adderall, Ritalin,
uh, Epitol, Loxitane...

06:51.041 --> 06:52.917
Olanzapine,
that shit was the worst.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.625
He blew up like a balloon
on that one.

06:54.709 --> 06:55.917
He'd be on his knees
every morning

06:56.000 --> 06:57.917
begging us
not to make him take it.

06:58.041 --> 06:59.709
GAYLE GRAHAM:
Did they help him at all?

07:00.834 --> 07:01.959
Some.

07:02.041 --> 07:05.667
This mood disorder,
is there a history of that...

07:05.750 --> 07:07.875
in your family,
outside of Kevin?

07:08.417 --> 07:09.542
Um...

07:11.959 --> 07:14.166
Well, my dad was depressed.

07:14.250 --> 07:16.834
He was never officially
diagnosed but my...

07:16.917 --> 07:19.500
my mother would just send him
out of the house when

07:19.583 --> 07:22.250
she'd notice him sinking.
And, uh,

07:22.333 --> 07:25.125
he'd go live with his brother
in Drexel Hill for...

07:25.208 --> 07:27.959
(INHALES) ...a few weeks
and come home when he, uh...

07:28.041 --> 07:30.667
-felt strong enough.
-And what about you?

07:32.792 --> 07:34.667
Any periods of depression?

07:35.375 --> 07:36.709
MARE: Um...

07:37.542 --> 07:38.959
(SCOFFS)

07:39.041 --> 07:41.875
Yeah. I mean,
there were times, you know.

07:44.417 --> 07:45.959
(SMACKS LIPS)
Yeah, thinking back...

07:47.417 --> 07:49.750
maybe I was.
I mean, I probably was.

07:50.917 --> 07:54.250
There was a period
after Siobhan was born

07:54.333 --> 07:57.375
and Kevin was starting
to become difficult and, uh...

07:59.583 --> 08:01.083
yeah. Um...

08:02.166 --> 08:04.125
But, you know,
growing up, my mom,

08:04.208 --> 08:06.834
she didn't have patience
for any of that.

08:06.917 --> 08:11.000
And she was overwhelmed
dealing with my dad, so...

08:11.083 --> 08:13.667
you know, I didn't wanna...
(EXHALES) ...burden her

08:13.750 --> 08:15.709
any more than she already was,
so I just...

08:17.083 --> 08:18.834
coped with it.

08:18.917 --> 08:21.625
Yeah? And how did your father
cope with it?

08:25.417 --> 08:26.917
Well, he shot himself.

08:28.667 --> 08:30.291
Yeah, I was 13 years old.

08:31.458 --> 08:32.792
I'm so sorry, Mare.

08:37.375 --> 08:40.291
That must have been so much
to carry as a young child.

08:40.959 --> 08:42.417
How did it make you feel?

08:43.542 --> 08:45.500
Like I wasn't enough for him.

08:53.792 --> 08:55.500
You think...

08:55.583 --> 08:58.667
maybe it's...
something you inherit.

09:00.667 --> 09:02.458
-Hmm?
-GAYLE: What?

09:02.542 --> 09:05.000
You know, suicide,
mental illness?

09:05.959 --> 09:07.583
'Cause I read
a bunch of articles

09:07.667 --> 09:08.834
about these scientists who think

09:08.917 --> 09:11.917
maybe it's... you know,
passed down

09:12.000 --> 09:14.291
from generation to generation.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.500
You think... maybe?

09:18.625 --> 09:19.834
GAYLE: What are you looking for

09:19.917 --> 09:21.500
when you're reading
these articles?

09:23.125 --> 09:24.166
Um...

09:25.667 --> 09:27.041
hope, I guess.

09:29.041 --> 09:31.542
GAYLE: Hope that your grandson
won't turn out like--

09:31.625 --> 09:32.667
Like my dad.

09:34.166 --> 09:35.291
Or Kevin.

09:37.500 --> 09:39.166
GAYLE: Does it worry you
that he might?

09:42.417 --> 09:43.667
Oh, God, yeah.

09:46.959 --> 09:48.041
I'm terrified.

09:51.625 --> 09:53.834
HELEN: Poor Betty Carroll.

09:53.917 --> 09:56.291
I mean, she was just going out
for cereal,

09:56.375 --> 09:59.208
and she had a heart attack
and crashed into that pole.

10:00.000 --> 10:01.625
Cheerios killed her.

10:01.709 --> 10:03.458
Well, not exactly, Mom.

10:03.542 --> 10:05.792
Mrs. Carroll was gonna have
a heart attack

10:05.875 --> 10:07.625
with or without the Cheerios.

10:07.709 --> 10:08.917
HELEN: Not necessarily.

10:09.000 --> 10:11.291
I mean, what if she saw a deer
or a raccoon in the road

10:11.375 --> 10:14.250
and, you know, it spooked her
enough that her heart exploded?

10:15.542 --> 10:17.417
MARE: Drew, go put
your jammies on, honey.

10:17.500 --> 10:18.625
DREW: In a second.

10:18.709 --> 10:20.667
No. That's what you said
ten minutes ago.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.625
Go put your pajamas on. Now.

10:22.709 --> 10:24.041
-Now. Go.
-Okay.

10:24.750 --> 10:26.083
Go, run.

10:26.166 --> 10:29.917
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON TV)

10:35.417 --> 10:38.291
-JOHN: Pass the damn ball!
-BILLY ROSS: Come on! Pass it!

10:39.709 --> 10:40.792
Do you like this?

10:40.875 --> 10:42.208
-Yeah.
-Yeah? Okay.

10:44.333 --> 10:46.041
-Ah.
-That's very pretty.

10:46.125 --> 10:48.417
That's beautiful. Bracelets?

10:51.834 --> 10:54.083
I watched
your documentary project.

10:54.583 --> 10:55.875
Oh, yeah?

10:55.959 --> 10:58.917
I thought it was beautiful,
Siobhan. I was so moved.

10:59.000 --> 11:00.083
It was really brave.

11:01.083 --> 11:02.125
Thanks.

11:02.208 --> 11:04.834
So, I had this media lab teacher
my freshman year,

11:04.917 --> 11:08.166
this brilliant, inspiring woman
named Meg Frawley,

11:08.250 --> 11:10.041
and she just took
the head position

11:10.125 --> 11:12.875
of Media Studies
at Cal Berkeley last year.

11:12.959 --> 11:15.500
I think you should talk to her.
You two would really hit it off.

11:16.500 --> 11:18.083
Cal Berkeley?

11:18.166 --> 11:20.583
-Like, in California?
-ANNE: Yeah, babe.

11:20.667 --> 11:22.458
(CHUCKLES) In California.

11:23.291 --> 11:25.583
I already submitted
my applications.

11:25.667 --> 11:27.500
Yeah, but just talk to her.

11:27.583 --> 11:30.166
And if you don't like
what she has to say,

11:30.250 --> 11:32.166
then I wasted 20 minutes
of your life

11:32.250 --> 11:33.625
and I'll make it up to you.

11:34.166 --> 11:35.166
Yeah?

11:35.750 --> 11:37.625
-Yeah.
-How?

11:38.625 --> 11:40.291
Well, I have to figure that out.

11:43.125 --> 11:44.917
She's so happy.

11:45.000 --> 11:47.125
She's been looking forward
to trying on those dresses

11:47.208 --> 11:48.208
all week.

11:48.291 --> 11:49.500
Don't tell her, but, uh,

11:49.583 --> 11:50.875
-we got a limo...
-(MARE GASPS)

11:50.959 --> 11:53.291
...to take her and her friend
to dinner and the prom.

11:53.375 --> 11:55.250
HELEN: (CHUCKLES)
Oh, that's wonderful.

11:55.333 --> 11:57.166
-She's gonna have a ball.
-MARE: Mm-mm.

11:57.250 --> 11:59.417
Okay, okay, okay, okay,
okay, okay, okay, okay.

11:59.500 --> 12:01.667
That's enough. All right,
time for bed.

12:01.750 --> 12:03.792
Let's say goodnight.
Say goodnight.

12:03.875 --> 12:05.583
-Goodnight, Ryan.
-Goodnight.

12:05.667 --> 12:07.000
-LORI: Bye, cutie.
-MARE: Brush your teeth.

12:07.083 --> 12:08.375
-Goodnight, pal.
-LORI: Sleep well.

12:08.458 --> 12:11.125
-MARE: Night.
-Anyone need a beer?

12:11.208 --> 12:12.750
-Yeah.
-I'd take another one.

12:12.834 --> 12:13.875
I'm good.

12:15.166 --> 12:16.792
Lori tell you the news, Mare?

12:17.333 --> 12:18.750
What news?

12:18.834 --> 12:21.333
We went to visit Kenny
over at Delaware County Prison

12:21.417 --> 12:24.291
the other day, and he asked us
if we would consider

12:24.375 --> 12:27.959
-taking Erin's son, DJ, in.
-Take him in?

12:30.333 --> 12:32.041
Like-- like adopt him?

12:33.542 --> 12:34.709
What'd you tell him?

12:36.375 --> 12:38.458
We told him
we'd think about it.

12:38.542 --> 12:40.250
Kenny still has to talk
to the lawyer.

12:41.542 --> 12:43.125
JOHN: Right now,
DJ's still living

12:43.208 --> 12:44.542
with Dylan and his parents.

12:45.542 --> 12:48.792
Do you think
Kenny ever hit her, John?

12:48.875 --> 12:50.959
-Erin?
-MARE: Come on.

12:51.041 --> 12:54.458
-We all know what he's like.
-(SIGHS)

12:54.542 --> 12:55.834
There were times we suspected

12:55.917 --> 12:57.542
-things weren't good, but...
-BILLY: Here you go.

12:57.625 --> 12:59.667
...Erin was tough,
like her mother.

12:59.750 --> 13:01.208
I mean, you remember Rachel.

13:01.291 --> 13:02.583
She didn't tell anybody
she had leukemia

13:02.667 --> 13:04.625
until she was going
into hospice.

13:04.709 --> 13:06.542
Erin was a lot like that.
She...

13:07.375 --> 13:08.709
she didn't like
to talk about stuff.

13:08.792 --> 13:11.625
No, but we all knew
he wasn't treating her right.

13:11.709 --> 13:14.667
Of course. That's...
why we took care of her.

13:14.750 --> 13:17.583
Erin even lived with Billy
for a little while.

13:18.458 --> 13:21.083
When did she live
with you, Bill?

13:21.166 --> 13:24.250
Oh... (CLEARS THROAT) ...God.
That was like, uh...

13:25.250 --> 13:27.583
three years ago. At least.

13:28.959 --> 13:30.750
What did she move in for?

13:32.500 --> 13:34.041
Well, her mother just died

13:34.125 --> 13:38.041
and Kenny was drinking a lot,
I think, and...

13:38.125 --> 13:40.333
and we didn't want her
around that.

13:40.417 --> 13:42.583
So I asked her
to come stay with me,

13:42.667 --> 13:45.041
and I fixed her up a room
in the basement.

13:45.125 --> 13:47.250
Mm. How long she stay?

13:49.166 --> 13:50.250
Uh...

13:51.583 --> 13:53.250
three weeks, maybe?

13:53.333 --> 13:54.667
It was little longer than that,
wasn't it?

13:54.750 --> 13:56.208
I thought it was at least
a couple months

13:56.291 --> 13:58.333
-she was with you.
-(BILLY SCOFFS)

13:58.417 --> 14:00.834
I really don't remember.
It was a long time ago.

14:04.250 --> 14:06.417
-I gotta get going.
-JOHN: Where are you going?

14:06.500 --> 14:10.041
BILLY: Uh,
Matty's having that fundraiser

14:10.125 --> 14:11.834
for his daughter
at the Duffer's.

14:13.875 --> 14:15.458
You know, I told him
I'd stopped by.

14:17.041 --> 14:18.542
-Have a good night.
-See you later.

14:18.625 --> 14:20.875
-Bye, Bill. Have fun.
-BILLY: Thanks. I will.

14:20.959 --> 14:21.959
Bye.

14:22.542 --> 14:23.834
(DOOR OPENING)

14:25.291 --> 14:27.166
(DOOR CLOSING)

14:27.250 --> 14:29.333
DYLAN HINCHEY: So I guess
you heard the news about DJ?

14:30.917 --> 14:32.792
BRIANNA DELRASSO:
What's gonna happen to him now?

14:32.875 --> 14:35.792
My parents and I met with
Child Youth Services yesterday.

14:37.542 --> 14:39.125
Your parents wanna keep him?

14:40.375 --> 14:43.417
Well... How do you feel
about that, like...

14:43.500 --> 14:45.834
having to see him every day
now that you know?

14:47.458 --> 14:50.500
I don't know.
It's fucking weird, you know?

14:53.291 --> 14:54.875
So what's your situation?

14:55.500 --> 14:57.542
Uh... (SCOFFS)

14:57.625 --> 15:00.792
...my lawyer thinks I can plead
down to a misdemeanor.

15:01.959 --> 15:03.000
We'll see.

15:06.375 --> 15:09.041
Either way, I'm not going
to college next year.

15:09.125 --> 15:11.750
Might just enroll in that
Hopkins Beauty School

15:11.834 --> 15:13.041
out on 352.

15:15.375 --> 15:17.333
My friend went there
and, uh...

15:18.834 --> 15:21.250
you know, she works in
a real good salon in Bryn Mawr.

15:23.875 --> 15:26.208
Doing hair for all
the rich Main Line women.

15:27.166 --> 15:28.875
(CHUCKLES)

15:28.959 --> 15:31.041
Just keep thinking
I'm gonna wake up and...

15:32.041 --> 15:33.417
it'll be like a bad dream.

15:38.125 --> 15:39.667
Bet you were scared, huh?

15:42.083 --> 15:43.208
Yeah.

15:44.959 --> 15:46.208
Listen...

15:50.375 --> 15:51.667
you know, Dylan...

15:53.375 --> 15:55.041
if you ever wanna talk
about it...

15:57.750 --> 15:59.625
you just need someone
besides your parents--

15:59.709 --> 16:01.917
I got other friends. (SNIFFLES)

16:05.542 --> 16:06.583
Look...

16:08.750 --> 16:10.834
it's just that we were dating,
what,

16:10.917 --> 16:13.875
two months before this happened?

16:13.959 --> 16:17.000
I'm just saying,
you don't gotta like

16:17.083 --> 16:19.083
come around here
if you don't want to.

16:30.917 --> 16:33.041
You know, there are things
from that night.

16:36.792 --> 16:38.458
When I woke up,
you weren't in bed.

16:39.917 --> 16:41.500
I was probably out
in the den feeding DJ.

16:41.583 --> 16:43.250
