-her church group and shit?
-TEENAGER 3: Yeah.

36:19.834 --> 36:22.959
She was like,
"Stay away from that priest."

36:23.041 --> 36:25.917
Apparently, he raped some
14-year-old girl

36:26.000 --> 36:27.667
-on a class field trip.
-Thanks. Thank you.

36:30.125 --> 36:32.291
-TEENAGER 3: What the fuck?
-TEENAGER 1:
Yeah, it's messed up.

36:32.375 --> 36:33.834
TEENAGER 3:
What a fucking sicko.

36:37.500 --> 36:38.792
Hey, Father.

36:38.875 --> 36:41.083
I heard you got yourself
a little alter girl.

36:41.166 --> 36:43.208
-(LAUGHING)
-TEENAGER 4: Fucking clown.

36:43.291 --> 36:45.375
TEENAGER 3: Yo! Yo!

36:45.458 --> 36:46.750
TEENAGER 4:
Ears not working, Father?

36:46.834 --> 36:49.041
Yo, I'm talking
to you, you fucking pervert.

36:49.125 --> 36:50.875
-TEENAGER 4: Answer him!
-TEENAGER 3: Fucking pervert.

36:50.959 --> 36:53.917
-You pedophile punk!
-(CAN CLATTERING)

36:54.000 --> 36:56.166
TEENAGER 3: Oh, you need a towel
to clean yourself up, Father?

36:56.250 --> 36:57.750
-TEENAGER 4: Come on.
-TEENAGER 3: Fuck you.

36:57.834 --> 36:59.041
(TEENAGERS LAUGHING)

37:21.834 --> 37:24.250
What are you reading them for?
Bring it over here.

37:24.333 --> 37:30.458
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:49.875 --> 37:52.875
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

37:56.208 --> 37:58.500
CHIEF CARTER: We're very sorry
about all of this.

37:58.583 --> 37:59.834
I'm sure you're aware

37:59.917 --> 38:02.125
of all the recent activity
with the missing girls.

38:02.208 --> 38:05.125
Oh, my husband is 77 years old.

38:05.208 --> 38:07.625
-Mmm.
-He's got dementia.

38:07.709 --> 38:11.667
Some nights he wanders out
after I've fallen asleep.

38:11.750 --> 38:15.333
And he forgets
which house is ours.

38:15.417 --> 38:19.583
What kind of idiot thinks
that he might be the murderer?

38:20.208 --> 38:21.417
(INHALES)

38:31.709 --> 38:34.750
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER
CONTINUES)

38:34.834 --> 38:36.208
(SNIFFLES)

38:37.583 --> 38:39.166
What the hell were you thinking?

38:39.250 --> 38:41.000
MARE: He was looking
in people's windows, Chief.

38:41.083 --> 38:43.125
-And I thought that--
-CHIEF: You thought what?

38:43.208 --> 38:45.834
-May--
-He was the one that went
down here kidnapping girls?

38:45.917 --> 38:47.959
The one who killed
Erin McMenamin?

38:48.041 --> 38:50.875
He can't even remember
which house is his.

38:52.208 --> 38:55.083
What did I tell you
about staying away, Mare?

38:55.166 --> 38:58.625
-I forget.
-Don't play that shit with me.

38:59.375 --> 39:00.417
Don't.

39:02.417 --> 39:03.959
Now, take your ass home.

39:05.625 --> 39:08.625
(SIREN WAILING)

39:22.834 --> 39:23.834
Mark?

39:25.083 --> 39:27.041
Everything all right?

39:27.125 --> 39:29.083
DEACON MARK: No,
just leave me alone, Dan.

39:29.166 --> 39:30.542
(SIGHS)

39:30.625 --> 39:32.583
FATHER DAN: Oh, my God.

39:32.667 --> 39:35.166
What-- Are you all right?
What happened?

39:35.250 --> 39:36.667
Just leave me alone, okay?

39:36.750 --> 39:38.291
DAN: No, please.
Just let me see it--

39:38.375 --> 39:39.583
Just leave! Go!

39:39.667 --> 39:42.208
DAN: All right, plea... Please.

39:48.208 --> 39:49.291
I can't. (CRIES)

39:49.375 --> 39:53.083
DAN: Just-- Hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

39:53.166 --> 39:54.834
MARK: I can't anymore.

39:55.542 --> 39:56.625
(SOBS)

39:58.917 --> 40:00.291
(GRUNTS)

40:01.250 --> 40:02.834
DAN: Let me see your face.

40:04.125 --> 40:06.375
-(SNIFFLES)
-DAN: Who did this?

40:06.458 --> 40:10.333
Look, come on. Come on.
Doesn't matter.

40:10.417 --> 40:12.875
(SIGHS)
We need to call the police.

40:12.959 --> 40:15.625
MARK: No. Dan, no. (EXHALES)

40:20.417 --> 40:22.750
I was with Erin
the night she was killed.

40:24.333 --> 40:25.375
With her?

40:41.709 --> 40:44.208
But you told me that you only
spoke to her on the phone.

40:44.291 --> 40:45.875
She called, upset. (SOBS)

40:47.166 --> 40:49.208
Said-- said to go
pick her up, so...

40:50.667 --> 40:52.834
uh, I drove to Sharp's Woods...

40:53.959 --> 40:56.000
and then I put her bike
in my trunk.

40:56.083 --> 40:58.458
And then I was gonna
drive her home, that's all.

40:58.542 --> 41:01.208
But then she got a message
from someone

41:01.291 --> 41:04.709
saying-- asking her to go out
to Brandywine Park.

41:04.792 --> 41:06.125
And then she said that she--

41:06.208 --> 41:07.917
She said that she wanted me
to drive her there.

41:08.000 --> 41:10.083
So I said, "Okay,"
and I drove her there.

41:10.166 --> 41:12.291
I mean, I tried-- I tried
to convince her to go home,

41:12.375 --> 41:14.333
but she was just-- I mean,
she was hysterical.

41:14.417 --> 41:19.125
Just hysterical. And then she,
um... she stormed off.

41:19.208 --> 41:20.750
DAN: Why didn't you go
to the police?

41:21.834 --> 41:23.750
Why didn't you tell them
all this?

41:24.750 --> 41:28.291
Wha-- I have
a previous accusation?

41:28.375 --> 41:30.917
That I have her bike
in my trunk?

41:31.583 --> 41:32.875
I was scared...

41:34.792 --> 41:37.250
-Till I threw it in the river.
-Oh. (SIGHS)

41:38.000 --> 41:39.375
MARK: I threw it in the river.

41:42.000 --> 41:43.041
Did you?

41:44.291 --> 41:46.291
What? Kill her?

41:51.959 --> 41:53.792
If I said no,
would you believe me?

41:56.166 --> 41:59.625
I just don't understand
why she's coming here.

41:59.709 --> 42:03.625
-I thought she was off the case.
-She is off the case.

42:03.709 --> 42:05.208
Well, you think
it's a very good idea

42:05.291 --> 42:07.125
for you to be going out
with her then?

42:07.458 --> 42:09.125
(SIGHS)

42:10.000 --> 42:11.834
JUDY: I know
you like her, Colin.

42:14.000 --> 42:15.458
How do you know I like her?

42:15.542 --> 42:18.125
I see the way you look at her.

42:18.208 --> 42:20.417
And because I know
you better than anyone.

42:21.458 --> 42:22.750
(CAR HORN HORNS)

42:24.166 --> 42:25.291
I don't know.

42:33.792 --> 42:37.500
Hey. Just be careful,
that's all.

42:38.250 --> 42:39.583
(SIGHS)

42:39.667 --> 42:41.709
My whole life's been
about being careful, Mom.

42:43.792 --> 42:45.166
Look how far that's gotten me.

42:52.291 --> 42:54.125
Fuck. Bye.

43:22.125 --> 43:24.083
Thanks for coming with me.

43:24.166 --> 43:26.041
Well, I'm the detective
on this case.

43:27.542 --> 43:30.917
-Of course.
-ALLIE: It was last April.

43:31.000 --> 43:32.959
I was out by the riverfront,

43:33.041 --> 43:36.667
and I don't normally hustle
out there, but...

43:36.750 --> 43:39.166
all my regulars cancelled
and I needed the money.

43:39.709 --> 43:41.166
All right.

43:41.250 --> 43:45.667
Uh, and this guy pulled up,
and he seemed normal.

43:46.458 --> 43:49.125
And, um, I got in.

43:49.208 --> 43:52.125
And he parked
over by the stadium.

43:52.208 --> 43:56.375
And, um... (SNIFFLES) ...I went
to get into the backseat,

43:56.458 --> 43:58.000
uh, to get undressed.

43:58.083 --> 44:00.291
And, uh, before
we could do anything,

44:00.375 --> 44:02.417
his hands were round my neck.

44:02.500 --> 44:06.083
I-- I thought my eyes were
gonna pop right out of my skull

44:06.166 --> 44:08.041
and everything went black.
And I...

44:09.000 --> 44:11.000
I just started kicking
and fighting

44:11.083 --> 44:13.041
and, you know,
anything I could do to survive.

44:13.625 --> 44:15.667
-MARE: Hmm.
-Um...

44:15.750 --> 44:18.792
And... and I must have hit him.

44:18.875 --> 44:20.542
'Cause, uh,
when I opened my eyes,

44:20.625 --> 44:21.959
he was holding his face.

44:22.041 --> 44:24.625
And I jumped out of the car
and I ran.

44:24.709 --> 44:27.458
What can you tell us
about him, Allie?

44:27.542 --> 44:30.208
Um, was he white? Black?

44:30.291 --> 44:32.625
-Um, he was white.
-MARE: Uh-huh.

44:32.709 --> 44:33.834
Um, he had a beard.

44:34.625 --> 44:37.083
Uh, he smoked Winstons.

44:37.166 --> 44:40.667
And the only reason
I even really noticed

44:40.750 --> 44:42.917
was 'cause my grandmother
was the only person

44:43.000 --> 44:44.583
I ever seen smoke Winstons.

44:44.667 --> 44:46.208
Do you remember anything
about the vehicle?

44:46.291 --> 44:49.291
-Anything specific?
-Um, it was a van.

44:50.208 --> 44:55.083
-What kind of van?
-Um, a work van, maybe?

44:55.959 --> 44:57.291
It was blue.

44:59.834 --> 45:03.250
I-- I wrote down
part of the license plate.

45:03.333 --> 45:06.041
I was scared
that he might come back again

45:06.125 --> 45:08.166
and look for me.

45:09.333 --> 45:11.291
-PA plate?
-ALLIE: Yeah.

45:13.125 --> 45:14.667
(SIGHS)

45:19.417 --> 45:21.083
Jose. It's Zabel.

45:21.166 --> 45:22.917
I need you to run a partial
through PennDOT

45:23.000 --> 45:24.834
and any LPR systems
in the county for me.

45:24.917 --> 45:26.917
We're looking for a blue
utility van,

45:27.000 --> 45:29.041
plate is "George, Henry, David."

45:30.959 --> 45:32.125
How long you think?

45:34.375 --> 45:35.458
All right. Thanks.

45:37.875 --> 45:38.917
Well?

45:39.000 --> 45:41.834
Uh, my guy's running the plates.
Two hours tops.

45:43.041 --> 45:44.125
Okay.

45:45.250 --> 45:46.333
Fine.

45:51.500 --> 45:53.291
MARE: Hey, I'm sorry
for the other night.

45:54.542 --> 45:56.458
ZABEL: You don't have anything
to be sorry for, Mare.

45:56.542 --> 45:59.041
Just being honest
about how you feel.

46:00.375 --> 46:03.667
-I just can't do all of that.
-All of what?

46:06.458 --> 46:07.709
MARE: What you want.

46:09.625 --> 46:10.875
How do you know what I want?

46:12.000 --> 46:13.875
My life's a shitshow, Zabel.

46:15.083 --> 46:17.417
I'm about to lose custody
of my grandson.

46:18.291 --> 46:19.709
I'm still working through

46:19.792 --> 46:23.041
unresolved issues from my son
who killed himself.

46:23.125 --> 46:26.709
And, uh, my ex-husband
basically lives in my backyard,

46:26.792 --> 46:29.375
so you're right, I don't know
what you want, but...

46:30.750 --> 46:31.875
I'm sure it's not that.

46:33.417 --> 46:35.458
You could have just said that
when I asked you out.

46:35.542 --> 46:38.083
MARE: I know. And I should have.

46:39.417 --> 46:41.250
But I just, uh...

46:41.333 --> 46:43.333
even if they did kick me
off the fucking thing,

46:43.417 --> 46:45.083
it's still my case.

46:45.166 --> 46:47.792
You know what it's like
when a case gets inside you

46:47.875 --> 46:48.917
like that?

46:50.333 --> 46:53.250
It's not a switch
you can just turn off.

46:57.917 --> 46:59.417
I didn't solve that case.

47:03.125 --> 47:04.208
What?

47:05.250 --> 47:06.917
The girl from Upper Darby.

47:08.542 --> 47:10.125
Her parents hired a P.I.

47:10.208 --> 47:11.792
'cause we weren't working
fast enough.

47:13.250 --> 47:17.041
Some fucking drunk ex-cop
looking to make some extra cash

47:17.125 --> 47:18.542
calls me out of the blue
one day,

47:18.625 --> 47:21.625
says he wants to compare notes.
Thinks he's got something.

47:23.375 --> 47:24.458
I ignored it.

47:27.625 --> 47:28.875
Couple weeks go by,

47:28.959 --> 47:31.083
I'm in the area,
so I drop by his house.

47:31.166 --> 47:34.208
And his sister's there
packing up the place.

47:34.291 --> 47:37.291
Says he's in hospice.
His liver gave out...

47:38.917 --> 47:40.625
but help myself to any files.

47:41.959 --> 47:45.083
So... find one marked "Zabel"...

47:46.000 --> 47:47.166
I take it home.

47:48.625 --> 47:50.834
Son of a bitch, if he didn't
piece it all together.

47:53.083 --> 47:55.291
Neighbor gave an alibi
that didn't check out.

47:56.458 --> 47:57.500
He caught it...

47:58.917 --> 48:00.000
I missed it.

48:01.625 --> 48:02.667
(SCOFFS)

48:05.291 --> 48:06.834
I filed a search warrant,

48:08.000 --> 48:09.208
we hit the perp's house,

48:09.291 --> 48:11.834
find the poor girl's shoe
in his bedroom, guy confesses...

48:12.959 --> 48:14.041
case closed.

48:16.458 --> 48:19.542
-Why'd you do it?
-ZABEL: I don't fucking know.

48:21.083 --> 48:24.000
I think I really just wanted
to do something great...

48:24.750 --> 48:26.000
for once in my life.

48:29.625 --> 48:30.667
Makes you feel any better,

48:30.750 --> 48:32.667
I hid drugs
on my grandson's mother.

48:34.125 --> 48:35.667
That's why they put me on leave.

48:38.959 --> 48:40.000
Wait, you serious?

48:44.208 --> 48:45.208
Holy shit.

48:47.792 --> 48:50.917
Doing something great
is overrated.

48:52.291 --> 48:56.709
'Cause then people expect that
from you... all the time.

48:58.083 --> 48:59.166
What they don't realize is

48:59.250 --> 49:00.709
you're just as screwed up
as they are.

49:04.208 --> 49:07.375
-(PHONE VIBRATING)
-Hang on.

49:08.792 --> 49:09.875
Zabel.

49:14.208 --> 49:16.125
All right, bye.

49:16.208 --> 49:18.041
Seven matches on blue vans
in the area

49:18.125 --> 49:20.083
the night of Erin's murder.
Got the addresses.

49:21.458 --> 49:23.041
Let's go knock on some doors.

49:32.667 --> 49:33.792
What was that for?

49:35.750 --> 49:37.291
How do you know what I want?

49:47.000 --> 49:48.250
(DOORBELL RINGING)

49:48.333 --> 49:50.917
MARE: Does that van over there
belong to you?

49:51.000 --> 49:52.375
HOMEOWNER: Uh, yes?

49:52.458 --> 49:55.083
-How long have you had it?
-About four years.

49:55.166 --> 49:57.542
I run my housekeeping business
out of it.

49:57.625 --> 50:00.041
Anyone else you work with
ever drive it?

50:00.125 --> 50:01.583
No. Just me and my sister.

50:02.500 --> 50:04.667
Does that van over there
belong to you?

50:05.834 --> 50:09.166
-It was my husband's.
-Your husband around?

50:09.250 --> 50:13.208
He died two years ago.
What's this about anyway?

50:13.291 --> 50:15.208
WAYNE POTTS: Am I in some sort
of trouble or something?

50:15.291 --> 50:17.083
No, you're not in any trouble,
Mr. Potts.

50:17.166 --> 50:18.750
We just need to get some
details from you.

50:18.834 --> 50:20.583
-Details about what?
-(DOGS BARKING IN DISTANCE)

50:20.667 --> 50:23.000
Might be easier
if we step inside.

50:23.083 --> 50:24.333
It would just take
a few minutes.

50:27.625 --> 50:30.291
(DOGS BARKING)

50:30.375 --> 50:33.166
♪ ("YOU'VE GOT ANOTHER THING
COMIN'" BY JUDAS PRIEST PLAYS) ♪

50:33.250 --> 50:36.625
♪ Act tough
Ain't room for second best ♪

50:38.083 --> 50:40.875
So, what can I do for youse?

50:40.959 --> 50:43.542
Is that your Ford
cargo van outside?

50:43.625 --> 50:46.041
Yeah. Though I wish it wasn't.
Thing's been nothing

50:46.125 --> 50:47.875
but a headache
since the day I got it.

50:47.959 --> 50:49.458
Are you the only one
who drives it?

50:49.834 --> 50:50.875
Just me.

50:52.875 --> 50:55.834
Would you mind turning the,
uh, music down for us?

50:55.917 --> 50:58.667
♪ As the world goes by
You're thinkin' like a fool... ♪

50:58.750 --> 51:00.500
Sure.

51:00.583 --> 51:04.083
♪ Out there is a fortune
Waitin' to be had ♪

51:04.166 --> 51:06.458
♪ If you think I'll let it go
You're mad ♪

51:06.542 --> 51:09.625
♪ You've got
Another thing comin' ♪

51:09.709 --> 51:12.041
♪ You've got
Another thing comin' ♪

51:16.750 --> 51:19.000
♪ You've got
Another thing comin' ♪

51:20.000 --> 51:22.500
♪ You've got
Another thing comin' ♪

51:23.500 --> 51:24.542
(WHISPERS) Mare.

51:27.000 --> 51:28.375
MARE: Zabel.

51:30.333 --> 51:31.500
No gun.

51:34.667 --> 51:36.166
♪ Comin' for you ♪

51:37.625 --> 51:39.583
♪ You've got
Another thing comin' ♪

51:39.667 --> 51:40.709
♪ Baby ♪

51:40.792 --> 51:42.166
(MUSIC STOPS)

51:55.041 --> 51:58.375
-Sorry about that.
-ZABEL: No problem.

51:58.458 --> 51:59.750
Is that a bar
you got back there?

51:59.834 --> 52:04.750
Yeah. Belonged to my uncle.
He owned it for 20 years.

52:04.834 --> 52:06.291
He wanted to hand it down
to his son,

52:06.375 --> 52:08.500
but his son didn't want
nothing to do with the place,

52:08.583 --> 52:12.166
so he turned it over to me
back in... 2016.

52:12.250 --> 52:14.667
-What you do for a living?
-Uh, I make deliveries for...

52:14.750 --> 52:18.041
(CHATTER CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

52:19.625 --> 52:20.709
What's wrong?

52:20.792 --> 52:23.458
People are here.
And he didn't chain us up,

52:23.542 --> 52:25.083
which means he wasn't
expecting them.

52:29.208 --> 52:31.417
(CLANKS)

52:31.500 --> 52:33.875
(SCOFFS) You still haven't
told me what this is about.

52:36.208 --> 52:40.083
(CLANKING)

52:41.250 --> 52:43.667
Busted radiator.
It's on the list.

52:43.750 --> 52:45.333
I got a sagging pipe upstairs.

52:45.417 --> 52:47.166
(CLANKING)

52:47.250 --> 52:49.458
-It's not moving anymore.
-Hit it harder!

52:55.458 --> 52:56.625
(CLANKING CONTINUES)

53:02.625 --> 53:06.083
-MARE: What's the camera for?
-WAYNE: My uncle installed them

53:06.166 --> 53:08.583
just to keep an eye on
the cash register and whatnot.

53:10.458 --> 53:12.959
-You live alone?
-(CLANKING)

53:13.041 --> 53:15.125
-Mr. Potts?
-(CLANKING INTENSIFIES)

53:15.208 --> 53:19.166
Yeah. Just me...
All by my lonesome.

53:21.959 --> 53:24.959
(CLANKING CONTINUES)

53:30.583 --> 53:31.625
Zabel.

53:32.625 --> 53:34.000
-(GUNSHOT)
-(GRUNTS)

53:34.667 --> 53:36.375
(GUNSHOTS)

53:39.250 --> 53:42.333
-Help!
-(PANTS)

53:42.709 --> 53:43.834
(MOANS)

53:44.583 --> 53:45.625
(GRUNTS)

53:45.709 --> 53:47.834
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

53:53.542 --> 53:56.500
(PANTS)

54:10.000 --> 54:11.417
-(KNOCKING)
-MISSY: Over here!

54:11.500 --> 54:15.375
-Let us out! Help!
-Open the door, please! Please!

54:27.083 --> 54:29.583
(PANTS)

54:42.166 --> 54:44.208
(CONTINUES PANTING)

55:18.583 --> 55:20.917
(PANTS)

55:49.333 --> 55:50.458
(GUN COCKS)

55:52.291 --> 55:54.625
(GUNSHOTS)

56:34.250 --> 56:36.333
(GUNSHOTS)

56:37.959 --> 56:39.125
(GRUNTS)

56:45.709 --> 56:47.458
MARE: Goddamnit! (GRUNTS)

56:54.917 --> 56:56.834
-(GUNSHOTS)
-(PANTING)

57:01.917 --> 57:03.250
-(GUNSHOTS)
-(GRUNTS)

57:05.583 --> 57:08.667
(PANTS)

57:13.667 --> 57:16.875
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

57:26.959 --> 57:28.542
(TIRES SCREECHING)

57:33.208 --> 57:34.875
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

57:35.917 --> 57:37.291
OFFICER 1:
Fall in! We need more backup!

57:37.375 --> 57:38.583
OFFICER 2:
I got someone on the ground.

57:38.667 --> 57:39.959
